                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine and regular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (luminous vivid red)</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11077Zadengel">Za-Dǝngǝl</persName> is
                        mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#16vb">16vb</locus>, 35vb, 83rb.
                        He is the scribe of some other Mss. (MY-019, AQG-002, MR-040,
                           AGM-001).<date>First half of the 19th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ካ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ካሕን፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#9ra">9ra</locus>, 24va)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ሕ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#24va">24va</locus>, 38rb, 75va)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ዲ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡ </expan> (<locus target="#26va">26va</locus>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሃ/ሃሌ</abbr> for <expan>ሃሌ ሉያ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#25rb">25rb</locus>, 25va, 26ra)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ፍ፡</abbr> for <expan>ፍቱሐ፡ ወንጹሐ ይረስዮ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ በድን፡ </expan> (e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#36rb">36rb</locus>, 36vb, 37ra)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors and the scribe; a
                           few lines on the incipit page, alternating with black lines; two initial
                           lines of each section of the text; names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118
                           (e.g., fols. 29rb, 31ra, 32va); elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals; some other words, e.g., hale luya (e.g.,
                           fols. 5va, 6rb, 8rb), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 24rb, 32ra, 75va), kǝśtat
                           (e.g., fols. 27vb, 45va, 49vb), wa-kāʿǝba (e.g., fols. 30rb, 32ra, 33rb),
                           qǝdmä wängel (e.g., fols. 29vb, 31vb, 34va).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Angular</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#122vb">f. 122vb</locus>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">Ownership note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘቀርን፡ ሰበር፡ ዘተሣየጥዋ፡ በንዋየ፡
                              ቤተክርስቲያን፡ ወስዩመ፡ ሀገር፡ ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል። ወቄስ፡ ገበዙ፡ ክብረ፡ አብ፡ ዘአጽሐፍወ[sic]፡ ፬ደቂቀ፡
                              ሀብተ፡ ጽዮን። ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ። ወዓዲ፡
                              በቃለ፡ ፫፻፲ወ፰ርቱዓነ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን። </q>
                           <note> The note mentions the church of St Michael of Qarn Sabar as the
                              owner. It also indicates that the Ms. was bought with “the money of
                              the church” and was commissioned “by four children of Habta Ṣǝyon”.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Corrections written interlineally: <locus target="#10rb">10rb</locus>, 19vb, 21va, 26rb, 27va, 34vb, 42rb, 49va, 50vb, 52ra,
                           80ra, 80vb, 82va, 104rb, 120rb.
 - Space for rubricated names left
                           unfilled: <locus target="#23va">23va</locus>, 72vb, 88ra, 101rb.
 -
                           The scribe used compressed script: <locus from="27vb" to="28ra">27vb-28ra</locus>, 45va-vb, 49vb-50ra, 51va-vb, 57rb, 58vb-59ra,
                           61va-vb, 117ra-va, 123ra-124va.
 - The word እገሌ is marked by thin
                           lines above and below on fols. e.g., 28ra, 29rb, 40va, 72va-vb,
                           73ra-rb.
 - Minor notes and writing exercises: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 11v, 86v, 87r, 95v.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Notes in the upper margins referring to the
                              content of the Ms.: fols. 7vb, 9va, 21ra, 23rb, 24vb, 28ra, 29vb,
                              31ra, 32va, 34ra, 37rb, 39rb, 39va, 42va, 47vb, 54rb, 56rb, 58ra,
                              59vb, 63ra, 64va, 66rb, 75rb, 79rb, 82ra, 83rb, 87vb, 88r, 94r, 114vb,
                              116ra, 117ra, 117va. - Coloured threads have been inserted in the
                              outer margin of fols. 26, 28, 42, 68, 75, 86, 114.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
